  "market_context": "On the daily chart, NQ1! was in a bullish order flow with consecutive closes above the previous day high, establishing PDH as the upside target. The analyst dropped to the 15-minute chart to frame a long entry for 7 May 2024.",
  "key_observation": "London did not set a tradeable low; instead it swept both sides of the range and moved lower, creating failure swings (equal highs near PDH). New York then swept external sell-side liquidity opposite to bullish order flow before reversing, forming a NY Manipulation profile and a 4H Power of Three.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Assessed daily chart order flow on NQ1! — observed consecutive closes above previous day high, confirming bullish bias and identifying PDH as the upside target.",
    "Step 2: Dropped to the 15-minute chart to determine whether London set a low to trade off of; observed that London instead swept the range to the downside and moved lower rather than forming a clean low.",
    "Step 3: Identified failure swings (equal highs) near PDH on the 15-minute chart after price moved back into the range, noting resting buy-side liquidity above.",
    "Step 4: Observed that as the New York session approached, price swept external sell-side liquidity (opposite to bullish order flow) — confirming the NY Manipulation profile.",
    "Step 5: Dropped to the 5-minute chart to identify the Change in State of Delivery (CHoCH) — located the point where price closed above a series of down-close candles, paired with a Fair Value Gap.",
    "Step 6: Planned two entries: one on the order block and one on the Fair Value Gap; both entries were tagged as price reversed higher.",
    "Step 7: Confirmed the structure as a 4-Hour Power of Three — the sweep lower was accumulation/manipulation and the rally to PDH was distribution.",
    "Step 8: Added confluence using standard deviation projections — the 2–2.5 SD level aligned with PDH and the 4–4.5 SD level aligned with the maximum expansion target."
  ],
  "outcome": "Both the order block entry and the Fair Value Gap entry were filled; price rallied and hit the take-profit at previous day high (PDH ~18200).",
  "lessons": "When daily order flow is bullish and London fails to set a clean low (instead sweeping both sides), wait for New York to make an opposing liquidity sweep. The CHoCH on the 5-minute chart paired with a Fair Value Gap provides a high-probability long entry targeting PDH, confirmed by the 4H Power of Three structure.",
